2 WEEKS from today I will officially be moving back to the DFW area!! 😍😍

And lots not forget the years of Television, Films, Commercial, and Voice Over work I’ve had the privilege on doing!! 😍

Plus being a Ghost-Writer! 👻📝
So, yeah... Definitely NOT my first job...! 😅😂😂
Along with SeaWorld I was at Majestic Theatre 🎭 for six months before all the COVID craziness~! 🦠 So sad I couldn’t watch more shows...! 😭
Adored the experience of scaring Guests at Howl-O-Scream (one of my favorite things at Universal’s HHN! 🎃) before getting to Twinkle~💖 with my girl, Abby-Cadabby in the Sesame Street Parade!
And because theme parks are just in my blood by this point, I was quickly hired into SeaWorld Entertainment! 🐳🖤

Lasted another 6months and realized the California Commercial & Television scene was not me me~ 😒😒

Returned to San Antonio, TX and was glad to be home. 🏠
Left parades after only 5months to act in California 📺 🎞, but also got to keep the magic alive by joining Attractions & Parades at DisneyLAND~! 🐭🖤❤️
After 1yr with Hogsmeade I got the chance to move over to Universal Studio’s SuperStar⭐️Parade! It was such a great opportunity to finally be apart of Theme Park Entertainment!! 💜💜
Along with Disney I worked @ Universal Studios Orlando at Flight Of The Hippogriff! 🖤✨ The Wizarding World of Harry Potter was my ultimate nerd-dreams come true~!

People forget I worked at Walmart for month, too!

Quit from Subway the summer before I moved to Florida even though I needed money. Thank gawd I was only on the Custodial Staff for a short while... People are crazy...! 🧼🧹
While I was a ~ Sandwich Artist ~ I became an Herbalife Distributor, tho that didn’t last long... The best friend still does it, but no thanks. Though I still love the shakes!🥤

1st “official” job as a big girl was Subway in Denton, TX while I was in school. 🦅💚
After 3 yrs of the smell I honestly can’t stand it now. 🤢
That’s also where I learned that I CANNOT work a desk job. So boring. AND I hate waking up early~! 😴...
1st job was technically my summer job with the step-mum as a filing clerk when I was 15yrs old. Did that every year up to 2019 just to help in the office and make a little extra 💰
Besides Acting, of course, I typically change jobs every 1-2years with the longest being Subway during my college days...! 🥖😅

Day 8 of Quarantine... The city has officially been announced for Shelter in Place... Not much in my life is going to change... Spent most of my day cleaning again. Finally got the monster of my bedroom done...

#QuarantineLife

I’ve heard him fighting with his toys (he gets very aggressive with them), push his food bowl back and forth inside the kennel just because, roll around several times because why not, and now he’s chewing on the bowl itself... 😅　#puppylife
But what’s funny is actually hearing him play and move around inside the kennel! Like, so THIS is what he actually does when he’s here alone for a couple hours! Lol 🐶

After spending the last 6hrs cleaning, I wanted to just relax in my room. So I’m now just lying on my bed, in the dark, while Conan’s in his kennel... I’m pretty sure he knows I’m in here, but it doesn’t seem to bother him at all...
I keep the room dark and quiet, away from where the rest of us are so he can fall asleep. Just as you would do with an infant human, right?

When I give Conan his meals I put him in his kennel and let him relax/nap for a couple hours. 🦴 He has so much puppy energy it sometimes drives the other dogs bonkers while they’re just trying to chill...

San Antonio just got the Shelter in Place order! So much for me deciding to finally turn my life around and join the outside world as an extroverted individual...! ✌🏼(￣▽￣)

Yesterday was about Cereal (I was hungry and eating cereal. Lol) and today it was finding a particular word for a particular type of Night Person mentality (for obvious reasons she says as she preps for bed finally at 5 AM). 🙂🙃

So there you have it! My random late night thoughts for today~! Or would you consider this early morning...??? Hmmmmm...
🤔
Then there's a whole other matter to discuss when we talk about late night mental work, like DREAMING orrrr Night Terrors and such, and that's always fun... but maybe for another time...??? ☁️

Not Night Owl or Insomniac orrr a NightTIME Person, & definitely not "Night Stalker." 😦

But a Night Person.🖤🌙

A person who mentally lives & works best at night and becomes more productive & proactive during those late night hours compared to the socially accepted daytime.

But not in that same context. When you hear that someone is a "Nighttime Person" you typically think of someone who's a Night Owl and the two are interchangeable, but now that I think about it, I think "Night Person" really fits what I'm looking for...

a Morning Person vs a Night Person.
 
We all fit into one category, though the hours we claim may be different... But that term. "Night Person." I think that's it...!

Curious, I Googled the thing. "Night Owl" and "Insomniac" are the only things that pop up for the most part, Night Owl being the (I suppose) technical term for what I'm looking for... But there was something else someone said.

I really don't know what it is, or why, but that's just how my brain works. I'm an "Average" kind of productive person when working during the daytime, but an "Exceptional" worker in the late-night hours. Technically, that's a Night Owl... But I don't like that word specifially.

For example, when I write:
I'll sit with a cuppa and my computer, everything turned off and my classical music playing, and only get out a couple hundred words...
Same scenario, after midnight though, and my fingers are flying across the keyboard with my mind racing...!
I am literally WAY more productive at night than during normal person hours when the sun is out, and my mind is overflowing with creativity during this time as well.

... and it's definitely on my mind but I'm not really into it... Buuuuut... as soon as the sun goes down and the clock strikes midnight I'm all in...!!
I can sit with a project for HOURS straight when its nighttime unlike during the day.

BUT! The word I'm looking for is for a very particular type of person. Because I am the type that is literally more productive at night than during the day...

Like, give me a project at 2PM and I can do it... I might procrastinate and do a little bit here or there...

DSPD: A Sleep Disorder that fluctuates & is manageable. Usually related to one's shifting work schedule and has everything to do with a person's INTERNAL CLOCK. Also, can be related to night people OR morning people!

⏰

Because here's what I think about when I hear these words:

Night Owl: Stays up later than the average person doing random stuff while the rest of the household sleeps. Always a choice. Makes person happy and they live an average/ positive night life...
🦉

It's me being a Night Owl that has really put me in the category of Delayed Sleep Phase Disorder, for sure, but at least it's something that can easily fluctuate with the proper mental training.
I also think that it's because of the DSPD that I'm curious about finding a word...

Then there's DSPD (Delayed Sleep Phase Disorder), which I kindaaaaa think I'm more under the umbrella for than Insomnia, to be honest. When I try to go to sleep during the TIME my brain is accustomed to, I have no problems... unlike the Insomniac would...

... While that same lack of sleep for the Insomniac doesn't help at all; on the contrary, Insomniacs are less active than the typical Night Owl because their mental stability isn't there since Insomnia is usually tied with other disorders.

When you choose to be a Night Owl you function normally throughout the day and stay up late at night, also living your normal lifestyle. You're used to getting less hours of sleep which is why you're able to function like a normal person...

When you have Insomnia you can be considered a Night Owl, but it's not your fault~! You have trouble falling/ staying asleep for whatever reason (there are a number of things that can cause Acute/ Chronic Insomnia), but it's a person's choice if they want to be a Night Owl...

On the other hand, an Insomniac is an actual sleep disorder and, although we joke about it, isn't always the best thing to have... It literally saps all your energy since you're not getting the full amount of rest your mind and body need; not to mention, it SUCKs. Lol

But Night Owls find it easy to stay up and hate mornings. Typically, Night Owls are people like Gamers who stay up laaaaate just doing whatever's on their mind.
They CAN wake up early and live a normal human day, they just don't prefer to...

To me, a "Night Owl" is someone who is CAPABLE of staying up late compared to an "Early Riser."
The Early Risers in my friends and family circle are literally INCAPABLE to staying up past a certain point (literally, like, 8-10PPM) which is crazy to me...

I know I'm a Night Owl. I hate waking up early in the mornings and, unlike normal people in my family, I am able to stay up late doing random things... And that's more of what I think of when I think of the term "Night Owl." 🦉
First thing that comes to mind is either "Night Owl" or "Insomniac," but neither of those fulfill exactly what I'm thinking about...
Is there a word for people who are mentally more proactive at night than the day???? 🦉🖤
